                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/16848</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-18">November 18,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Chinese Ambassador called at my request and I gave him the substance of my
                    statement to the British Minister a few minutes before,<note n="42"
                        xml:id="d453fn42">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> except that I did not refer
                    specifically to the last remarks between me and the Japanese officials about a
                    temporary arrangement such as I described in my talk with the British. This
                    matter was not immediately pertinent to the Chinese angle.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
